{{infobox Chinese|l=Yang Water Rat|kanji=壬子|romaji=mizunoe nezumi|onyomi=jinshi|p=rénzǐ|w=jen-tzŭ|mi=ʐən³⁵ tsɨ|y=jam4 zi2|j=jam4 zi2|ci=jɐm tsi|mc=ɲiɪm tsi|oc-bs=ɲɨm tsi}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}

'''Yang Water Rat also known as 壬子''' (mizu no ene, jinsui no nezumi, jinsui no ne, jinshi) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 49th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Xinhai|ja|辛亥}} and followed by {{ill|Guichuu|ja|癸丑}}. In the context of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Ren|ja|壬|1=Mizunoe (壬)}} represents yang {{ill|Water|ja|水}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Rat|ja|子 (十二支)|lt=Rat|lt_ja=子}} represents yang {{ill|Water|ja|水}}, resulting in a harmonious relationship ({{ill|Hiwa|ja|比和|lt=Hiwa|lt_ja=比和}}).  
==Yang Water Rat (壬子)'s Years==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 52 when divided by 60 is a {{ill|year|ja|年}} of {{ill|Jinshi|ja|壬子}}.
